I'll retry the network_fetcher tool with the required source parameter and specify the format in options to match the expected CSV format.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "options": {
    "format": "csv"
  }
}
</tool_call>

            I'll use the data_processing_validator tool to validate the retrieved data, as it has the highest relevance for data validation. Since it requires a schema, I'll use a default schema for CSV data.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "data": "data/output.json",
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "columns": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      "rows": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
          "type": "array"
        }
      }
    },
    "required": ["columns", "rows"]
  }
}
</tool_call>

I see that data_processing_validator requires data_processing_parser to be executed first. I'll execute the parser tool to prepare the data for validation.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/output.json"
}
</tool_call>

Now that the data has been parsed, I'll retry the data validation step with the parsed data.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "data": "data/output.json",
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "columns": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      "rows": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
          "type": "array"
        }
      }
    },
    "required": ["columns", "rows"]
  }
}
</tool_call>
